A lorry fire has resulted in the closure of the M74 motorway in both directions in South Lanarkshire.
A police spokesman said emergency services were called to the scene, near junction 10, at about 10:30. The motorway is closed between J9 and J12.
There were no reports of anyone being injured but local diversions have been put in place while emergency services deal with the incident.
Traffic is tailing back on the north and southbound carriageways.
